  <static seed="290" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/MixedNumberAdditionWordProblems10.pg">
    <statement><p>Each page of a book consists of a header, a footer and the middle part. The header is <m>{{\frac{5}{6}}}</m> inches in height; the footer is <m>{{\frac{7}{12}}}</m> inches in height; and the middle part is <m>{4{\textstyle\frac{5}{6}}}</m> inches in height.</p>
<p>What is the total height of each page in this book? Use mixed number in your answer if needed.</p>
<p>Each page in this book is <fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> inches in height.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>6{\textstyle\frac{1}{4}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We add up the height of the header, middle part and footer to find the total height of a page:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{5}{6}}} + {4{\textstyle\frac{5}{6}}} + {{\frac{7}{12}}}
      \amp =    {{\frac{5}{6}}} + 4 + {{\frac{5}{6}}} + {{\frac{7}{12}}} \\
      \amp =    4 + {{\frac{5}{6}}} + {{\frac{5}{6}}} + {{\frac{7}{12}}} \\
      \amp = 4 + \frac{5\cdot2}{6\cdot2} + \frac{5\cdot2}{6\cdot2} + \frac{7}{12}  \\
      \amp = 4 + \frac{10}{12} +  \frac{10}{12} + \frac{7}{12} \\
      \amp = 4 + \frac{10+10+7}{12} \\
      \amp = 4 + \frac{27}{12} \\
      \amp = 4 + \frac{9}{4} \\
      \amp = 4 + 2 \frac{1}{4} \\
      \amp = {6{\textstyle\frac{1}{4}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Each page in this book is <m>{6{\textstyle\frac{1}{4}}}</m> inches in height.</p>
</solution>
